# Wanix iframe isolation

Wanix **must** run in its own document, loaded via **iframe** (`src="/wanix.html"`), not in the same JS realm as the React cafe.

## Why

`wanix.min.js` pollutes the shared global namespace. Co-loading it on [`cafe/index.html`](../../cafe/index.html) alongside React/Vite/ZSS breaks or races the main app.

| Global / side effect | Risk |
|----------------------|------|
| `window.__wanix` | Wanix system registry |
| `window.Go` | Go `wasm_exec` injected into `<head>` at runtime |
| `customElements.define(...)` | Six Wanix tags — permanent, cannot unregister |
| `globalThis.list/read/write/bind/...` | DevTools helpers when `debug` is set |
| `window.WanixSocket`, AMD `require` (workbench) | More globals on `window` |

Separate document (iframe or navigation to `/wanix.html`) = clean `window` per realm.

## Prohibited

- `<script src="…/wanix.min.js">` in [`cafe/index.html`](../../cafe/index.html) or any cafe React entry
- `<wanix-system>` (or other Wanix custom elements) in React/TSX under `cafe/`
- Importing Wanix runtime into the Vite bundle for the main app

## Required

| Piece | Location |
|-------|----------|
| Canonical Wanix host | [`cafe/wanix.html`](../../cafe/wanix.html) — kernel, `<wanix-system>` tree, tasks, VMs |
| Cafe ↔ Wanix bridge | `zss/feature/wanix/` — iframe host + `postMessage` RPC (parent on `/`, child in iframe) |
| JSX types for Wanix tags | [`zss/feature/wanix/wanixelements.d.ts`](../../zss/feature/wanix/wanixelements.d.ts) |

## Examples

```text
❌ BAD — wanix.min.js in index.html; WanixSystem in React tree
✅ GOOD — hidden iframe src="/wanix.html"; bridge in zss/feature/wanix/
✅ GOOD — direct visit /wanix.html for Wanix-only debugging
```
